Windows are double-paned to reduce noise, but I would request a room on the left wing as you face Reception farther from the runways if you want to nap during the day.	The modest comp breakfast satisfies, the burgers at the pool bar are super and the airport noise is a non issue in the rooms due to excellent double paned windows.	The only complaint I have was that the maid came early in the morning twice and opened the door with a fast knock while we were sleeping.